<div class="container-fluid">
  <div class="container mst-container-main">
    <div>

      <h1><a href="/data/{{data.currentYear}}" class="label label-danger">{{data.totalCurrentYear}}</a> U.S. mass
        shootings in {{data.currentYear}}</h1>
      <h1><a href="/data/all" class="label label-danger">{{data.totalAllYears}}</a> mass shootings since 1/1/2013</h1>
      <h1><a href="/data/{{data.currentYear}}" class="label label-danger">{{data.daysSince}}</a> {{data.daysLabel}}
        since last mass shooting</h1>

      <br>
      <div class="row"><div class="col-sm-1"></div>
        <div class="col-sm-2">
          <a class="btn btn-danger btn-sm pull-right" href="/data">See the data</a>
        </div>
        <div class="col-sm-2">
          <button class="btn btn-primary btn-sm" id="fb-share"><i class="fa fa-facebook"></i> Share on Facebook</button>
        </div>
        <div class="col-sm-2">
          <a href="https://twitter.com/share" class="twitter-share-button pull-left" data-text="There have been {{data.totalCurrentYear}} mass shootings in {{data.currentYear}}." data-via="massshootingtrk" data-size="large" data-related="massshootingtrk" data-hashtags="massshootingtracker">Tweet</a>
        </div>
        <div class="col-sm-6"></div>
      </div>
      <p class="mst-shooting-definition">
        The Mass Shooting Tracker is a crowd-sourced database of U.S. mass shootings. We define a “mass shooting” as a
        single outburst of violence in which four or more people are shot. This is not the same as mass
        murder as defined by the FBI. <a href="/about">Learn more here.</a>
      </p>

      <div class="jumbotron">
        <h3>Faces of mass shootings</h3>
        <div id="carousel-example-generic" class="carousel slide" data-ride="carousel" data-interval=false>
          <!-- Indicators -->
          <ol class="carousel-indicators">
            <li data-target="#carousel-example-generic" data-slide-to="0" class="active"></li>
            <li data-target="#carousel-example-generic" data-slide-to="1"></li>
          </ol>

          <!-- Wrapper for slides -->
          <div class="carousel-inner center" role="listbox">
            <div class="item active" style="background-image:url(/img/family.png);">
              <div class="carousel-caption">
                Cynthia Villegas and her four daughters were murdered on 6/11/2016
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="item" style="background-image:url(/img/family2.jpg);">
              <div class="carousel-caption">
                The mother and four children were shot to death in their New Mexico home.
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Controls -->
          <a class="left carousel-control" href="#carousel-example-generic" role="button" data-slide="prev">
            <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-chevron-left" aria-hidden="true"></span>
            <span class="sr-only">Previous</span>
          </a>
          <a class="right carousel-control" href="#carousel-example-generic" role="button" data-slide="next">
            <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-chevron-right" aria-hidden="true"></span>
            <span class="sr-only">Next</span>
          </a>
        </div>
        <br>

        <p>Juan David Villegas-Hernandez shot dead his wife Cynthia Villegas and her four daughters in
        their New Mexico home. Court documents show that he may have been headed for a divorce.</p>
        <p>“We’re just gonna get all that money that we want to raise, we’re gonna get it to this family so
          they don’t have to worry about nothing but having five beautiful funerals,” said Nicole Vargas, family friend.</p>
        <p>The story was reported in three local news outlets and a blurb in the Associated Press.</p>
        <p><a class="btn btn-primary btn-lg" href="#" role="button">Previous mass shootings</a></p>
      </div>

      {{>recentshootings}}

      <div class="row bottom-row">
        <div class="col-sm-12">
          <a class="btn btn-large btn-danger" href="/data">See the data</a>
        </div>
      </div>

    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<script>
document.getElementById('fb-share').onclick = function() {
  FB.ui({
    method: 'share',
    display: 'popup',
    quote: 'There have been {{data.totalCurrentYear}} mass shootings in {{data.currentYear}}.',
    hashtag: '#massshootingtracker',
    href: 'https://massshootingtracker.org',
  }, function(response){});
}
</script>
